defs.docs:
Termion is a pure Rust, bindless library for low-level handling, manipulating
 and reading information about terminals. This provides a full-featured
 alternative to Termbox.

defs.docs: Get the size of the terminal.

defs.name: HideCursor
defs.docs:
Hide the cursor for the lifetime of this struct.
 It will hide the cursor on creation with from() and show it back on drop().

defs.name: RawTerminal
defs.docs:
A terminal restorer, which keeps the previous state of the terminal, and restores it, when
 dropped.

defs.docs: Managing switching between main and alternate screen buffers.

defs.name: ToAlternateScreen

defs.name: AlternateScreen
defs.docs:
A terminal restorer, which wraps a type implementing Write, and causes all writes to be written
 to an alternate screen.

defs.name: from
defs.docs:
Create an alternate screen wrapper struct for the provided output and switch the terminal
 to the alternate screen.
